changing the history of the project


Amending
<!-- it will modify it -->

git commit --amend

git commit --ammend -m 'new commit'
git commit --ammend --no-edit


it will undo the changes it didnt delete the file it make it into the the orignal state 

git reset

it will delete all the commits you make changes to your file
git reset --hard 



Rebasing

it is design to commit from one branch to another
used to completely rewrite the history of commits

git rebase <Branch>/<commit>
git rebase --interactive <Branch>/<commit>
<!-- limited commits where you put hte number head~2 or 3 -->
git rebase -i HEAD~#
<!-- it will bring all the commits -->
git rebase -i --root
